The paper deals with geometric and topological data analysis, specifically the Reeb graph as a descriptor for scalar functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer science sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper discusses stability and robustness of the Reeb graph, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions an application of the results to simplification schemes, which could fall under the sub-categories of graphics (cs.GR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
